Mumias police yesterday gunned down an armed robber at Mwitoti shopping centre.Mumias East subcounty AP commander Ezekiel Ogutu said Idris Mutimba&rsquo;s two accomplices fled. He said police on patrol were alerted about the robbery by a watchman. &ldquo;Police confronted the three and told them to surrender, but they refused to do so,&rdquo; Ogutu said. He said Mutimba&rsquo;s accomplices were at the back of the shop and escaped before police opened fire.Ogutu said Mutimba was a notorious criminal who dropped out of Eluche Primary School. He said Mutimba had earlier attacked a Chinese worker at a construction site near Shianda market.Police recovered a hacksaw used to cut padlocks at the shop&rsquo;s entry. Mutimba said the thugs took advantage of the Manchester versus Liverpool match to rob shops.